      "writtenOn": "2017-10-16T16:34:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this code got complex for the benefit of doing one Get instead of two in a non-perf critical code.\n\nalso, i think storing buildSummaries is not buildstore\u0027s job\nbuildstore is defined as\n\"Package buildstore implements storage of //milo/api/buildbot/* types.\"\nhttps://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/milo/buildsource/buildbot/buildstore\nbuildSummary is a concept common to buildbot and non-buildbot, so I think putting buildSummary is the responsibility of SaveBuilder\u0027s caller. Looking at this transactional code, I see no logic that would prevent that (except, it should happen in the same transaction).\n\nConsider:\n- SaveBuilder: panic if called not in a transaction (datastore.CurrentTransaction)\n- SaveBuilder: return build key\n- SaveBuilder callsite: start a new transaction, call SaveBuild, save buildSummary",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 206,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 208,
        "endChar": 80
      },
      "revId": "2ab3367ad579e75fb9a52a6d723b692ce0754da2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "29c51cfc_c4b5f564",
        "filename": "milo/buildsource/buildbot/buildstore/build.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 208,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-17T22:36:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Discussed offline, but going to keep this here for now. The BuildSummary can (should) be thought of as a specialized index on all build objects inside of milo (regardless of underlying implementation). Keeping that index up to date makes sense for this package:\n  * summarization is a pure function of the build\n  * saving a build without updating the summary would be a bug (e.g. external summarization, external transaction)",
      "parentUuid": "6e53262d_73248620",
